Does 7.1 == 7.10 return true?

If you are a java.math.BigDecimal, and someone sends you .equal(), you won&#39;t
think so.

This is a precision issue ... and yes, if you&#39;re storing data that
inherently requires fixed-width precision, such as Money, you should always
think twice before considering float or double.

